text: "A health worker had a needle stick injury. While handling a chronic Hepatitis B case. She has taken 2 complete schedules (6 doses) of HBV vaccination. She was tested and was diagnosed as a non-responder to vaccination 3 months back, What is the most appropriate management in this case:",
options: [{"id": "A", "text": "Give 2 doses of HBIG one now and another 4 weeks later", "is_correct": true}, {"id": "B", "text": "Give 2 doses of HBIG now (stat)", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "C", "text": "Give HBV vaccination starting now, after 4-6 weeks, check HBV titres and decide on giving HBIG", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "D", "text": "HBIG single dose with HBV vaccination (first dose beginning now)", "is_correct": false}],
explanation: "A documented vaccine non-responder exposed to an HBsAg-positive source requires **passive immunization only**. Two doses of HBIG are given: one immediately and another at 1 month, as further vaccination is ineffective in proven non-responders. HBIG provides immediate anti-HBs protection after high-risk exposure. Revaccination strategies are used only in unknown or incomplete responders, not confirmed non-responders.<br><br>| **Criteria** | **Meaning** |\n| -------- | ------- |\n| Anti-HBs <10 mIU/mL | No protective immunity |\n| After 2 full vaccine series | True non-responder |<br><br><img src=\"https://corebtr-assets-production.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/question_explanation/4c8d473c-c2a4-412b-8ff8-78cc9ef15082.png\" alt=\"Uploaded Image\">Non-responder : anti-HBs < 10 after 2 full series\nWhat to do: HBIG \u00d7 2 doses: 4 weeks apart; No further vaccine",
